instruct_text: In this experiment, you will be assuming the perspectives of various jobs while listening to short stories.
There are 4 parts of the experiment, and, before you begin, we'll give you a brief overview of all the parts.
In the first part, you'll be introduced to the perspectives of 8 different jobs.
For each short story, you'll be assigned one of these perspectives to assume while you listen to it.
The 4 questions for each perspective are learned with quizzes in this first part of the experiment.
In the second part of the experiment, you will listen to 8 short stories.
You will hear each sentence of the story played individually.
The sentence will play fully, and, when the sentence has finished playing, you will press a button to advance to the next sentence.
Before listening to each story, you will be assigned one of the eight perspectives to take on while listening to it.
You'll be given a quiz before the story on the 4 questions associated with the assigned perspective.
You must pass this quiz to move onto the story.
You'll be given a blank text box under the image, where you can type out all the details of the story you can remember.
There is a 5 minute time limit for recalling each story.
In the fourth part of the experiment, you will be asked questions about each story.
You'll type your answers to the questions in a text box.
Questions?
Let's begin Part 1!
The 8 perspectives are as follows:
You’ll become acquainted with these perspectives more in the following quizzes where you’ll learn the 4 questions associated with each perspective.
For each perspective, you'll go through all four questions in a sequence.
Then you'll get the quiz and indicate which questions you saw in the order in which they appeared in the sequence.
You'll indicate the question you select by pressing the number key corresponding to the number in front of the question.
If you indicate the wrong question during the quiz, you'll get the questions presented in the correct order again and restart the quiz.
After you've passed the quizzes for each perspective, you'll do all of the quizzes a final time but without seeing the correct order of the questions beforehand.
Press space to begin the quizzes!

instruct_text: Great job! You’ve finished the quizzes and Part 1. Please notify the researcher that you have finished.
Let's begin Part 2!
You are about to begin the second part of the experiment, where you will listen to the short stories.
As a reminder, you'll be assigned a perspective and given the corresponding quiz before each story.
The stories will be presented to you sentence by sentence, such that you will listen to each sentence individually.
IMPORTANT! While listening to each story, you will additionally have to make a judgement about each sentence in order to advance to the next sentence.
Some people feel that the stories have natural “parts.” We want you to make a judgement about when you think the story has transitioned from one “part” to another.
You will press “9” if you think the sentence you just listened to has begun a new “part” of the story.
For example, you should press “9” at the beginning of a story and when you think a different “part” in the story has begun.
You will press “1” if you think the sentence was in the same “part” as the sentence that came before it.
There are no “right” answers. We want to see what you think these parts are.
Once you make the decision that each sentence has begun a new part of the story or not by pressing 9" or "1"
rolePic: the next sentence in the story will begin to play. "

instruct_text: You will not be able to go back to previous sentences or change the judgement you made about a previous sentence.
Please use both index fingers during the story listening, with one resting on the “1” and the other on the “9.”
You will not be able to make your judgement about whether the sentence begins a new part or not until the sentence has finished playing.
Questions?
